f=Brand Studio/atlas/marketplace/brand-identity/references/contrast-and-accessibility.md · h1:Contrast Accessibility Brand Identity=brand color choice fails accessibility design defect. product, page, button, label using color inherits failure. reference walks through math, standards, practical implications. · h2:The math=`(L1 + 0.05) / (L2 + 0.05)` · h2:The math=`function contrast(bg, fg) { \· function lum(hex) { \· return [hex.slice(1,3), hex.slice(3,5), hex.slice(5,7)] \· .map(h => parseInt(h, 16) / 255) \· .map(v => v <= 0.03928 ? v / 12.92 : Math.pow((v + 0.055) / 1.055, 2.4))` · h2:The math=Contrast ratio calculated as: relative luminance lighter color darker. Relative luminance comes weighted formula RGB values accounts human perception (green contributes blue). **Quick contrast checker (run browser console):** · h2:The "darker variant" strategy=`Brand orange (signature):    #FF9900   (used in logos, illustrations, large graphics) \· Brand orange (text/UI):      #B86600   (passes AA against white)` · h2:The "darker variant" strategy=brand colors fail contrast, define darker variant use text UI. "the brand color." signature version what people associate brand. text variant what enables accessible without abandoning identity. standard practice. major brands versions, even signature version publicized. · h2:Typography contrast=Type contrast about color. includes: · h2:Typography contrast=**Color contrast** (per standards above), **Weight contrast** (light text busy background fails even high color contrast), **Size contrast** (very small text needs higher color contrast) · h2:Typography contrast=**Practical rules:** · h2:Typography contrast=Body text: minimum 14px web, ideally 16px. Below 14px uncomfortable readers regardless contrast., Body text photographs busy backgrounds: add scrim, increase type weight, move text., Light-weight fonts (Thin, Extra Light) body text: avoid. They fail visual contrast even passing color contrast. · h2:Icons and graphical elements=WCAG requires 3:1 components graphical elements. includes: · h2:Icons and graphical elements=Icons used convey meaning, Form field borders, Focus indicators, Chart elements distinguish data series, Toggle and switch states · h2:Icons and graphical elements=**Common failure:** · h2:Icons and graphical elements=Light gray icon (#D1D5DB) white background: 1.4:1. Invisible users low vision., Form field borders #E5E7EB: 1.3:1. Borderline visible. · h2:Icons and graphical elements=**Fix:** · h2:Icons and graphical elements=Icons convey meaning: minimum #6B7280 white (3.9:1)., Form field borders: minimum #9CA3AF white (3.0:1) default state. Stronger focus. · h2:Resources=WebAIM Contrast Checker (free, browser-based), Stark plugin for Figma, Chrome DevTools accessibility panel, Coblis color blindness simulator, WCAG 2.1 specification w3.org